Air Products & Chemicals, Inc.


                  Company Overview

Air Products touches the lives of consumers around the globe in positive ways every day. With over 20,000 employees and operations in more than 50 countries, we serve customers across a wide range of industries from food and beverage, health and personal care to energy, transportation and semiconductors. We supply a unique portfolio of atmospheric gases, process and specialty gases, performance materials, equipment and services.

Founded in 1940, Air Products has built a reputation for its innovative culture, operational excellence and commitment to safety and the environment. Our aim is to develop lasting relationships with our customers and communities based on human qualities: understanding their needs, doing business with integrity and honesty, and demonstrating a passion for exceeding expectations.                





 Boards & Committees



Corporate Boards ▾




Lead Director, Board of Directors

                    2008 - Current                  


KMG Chemicals, Inc.

                    KMG Chemicals, Inc. manufactures and distributes specialty chemicals. It operates through the following segments: Electronic Chemicals, Wood Treating Chemicals and Industrial Lubricants. The Electronic Chemicals segment sells wet process chemicals primarily to the semiconductor industry. These are used to clean and etch silicon wafers in the production of semiconductors. The Wood Treating Chemicals segment produces and supplies pentachlorophenol, a specialty chemical for industrial wood treating applications. The Industrial Lubricants segment provide products and services for industrial valve and actuator maintenance. This segment product portfolio includes valve lubricants, cleaners and sealants, as well as related products such as fittings, adapters and application equipment The company was founded in 1992 and is headquartered Fort Worth, TX.                  




Independent Non-Executive Director

                    2010 - 2014                  


AZ Electronic Materials SA

                    AZ Electronic Materials SA develops and manufactures antireflective coatings and ancillary chemicals, which are used in integrated circuits, devices, flat panel displays and photographic printing. The company was founded in 1957 and is headquartered in Luxembourg.                  




Director

                    2007 - 2014                  


Az Electronic Materials Usa Corp.

                    AZ Electronic Materials USA Corp. develops and manufactures technology products for use in integrated circuits and devices. The firm's products are used in the manufacture of flat screen digital TV's, PC's, mobile phones, navigation devices, and medical imaging equipment. The company has facilities in China, the United States, Japan, Korea, France, Germany, Singapore, Hong Kong, and the United Kingdom. The company is located in Branchburg, NJ.                  





